api_list.name: createAgreement
api_list.description: Creates a billing agreement for the buyer.

required_parameters.name: accessToken
required_parameters.description: accessToken obtained with clientId and secret.

required_parameters.name: description
required_parameters.description: Description of the agreement. Maximum length: 128.

required_parameters.description: Json object. A resource representing a Payer that funds a payment. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

required_parameters.description: Name of the agreement. Maximum length: 128.

required_parameters.name: plan
required_parameters.description: Json object. Billing plan resource that will be used to create a billing agreement. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

required_parameters.name: startDate
required_parameters.description: Start date of the agreement. Date format yyyy-MM-dd z, as defined in ISO8601. Format: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSTimeZone.

optional_parameters.name: agreementDetails
optional_parameters.description: Json object. A resource representing the agreement details. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: sandbox
optional_parameters.description: Use sandbox to tests. Set 1 to enable.

optional_parameters.name: overrideChargeModels
optional_parameters.description: Array of json objects. A resource representing an override_charge_model to be used during creation of the agreement. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: overrideMerchantPreferences
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Resource representing merchant preferences like max failed attempts,set up fee and others for a plan. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: shippingAddress
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Base Address object used as billing address in a payment or extended for Shipping Address. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createAgreement README for more details.

api_list.name: createCreditCard
api_list.description: Stores credit card details with PayPal.

required_parameters.name: expireYear
required_parameters.description: The 4-digit card expiry year.

required_parameters.name: accessToken
required_parameters.description: accessToken obtained with clientId and secret.

required_parameters.name: type
required_parameters.description: Credit card type. Allowed values: visa, mastercard, amex, discover, maestro.

required_parameters.name: expireMonth
required_parameters.description: Expiration month with no leading zero.

required_parameters.name: number
required_parameters.description: Credit card number. Valid value is numeric characters with no spaces or punctuation. The string must conform with modulo and length required by each credit card type.

optional_parameters.name: merchantId
optional_parameters.description: ID of the merchant for which to list credit card resources.

optional_parameters.name: externalCardId
optional_parameters.description: Externally provided ID of the card for which to list credit card resources.

optional_parameters.name: billingAddress
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Base Address object used as billing address in a payment or extended for Shipping Address. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createCreditCard README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: firstName
optional_parameters.description: The first name of the card holder. Maximum length is 25 characters.

optional_parameters.name: externalCustomerId
optional_parameters.description: Externally provided ID of the customer for which to list credit card resources.

optional_parameters.name: cvv2
optional_parameters.description: The 3 to 4 digit card validation code.

optional_parameters.name: sandbox
optional_parameters.description: Use sandbox to tests. Set 1 to enable.

optional_parameters.name: payerId
optional_parameters.description: unique ID that you can assign and track when you store a credit card or use a stored credit card.

optional_parameters.name: lastName
optional_parameters.description: The last name of the card holder.

api_list.name: createInvoice
api_list.description: Creates a draft invoice.

required_parameters.name: merchantInfo
required_parameters.description: Json object. Merchant business information that appears on the invoice. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

required_parameters.name: accessToken
required_parameters.description: accessToken obtained with clientId and secret.

optional_parameters.name: paymentTerm
optional_parameters.description: Json object. The payment term of the invoice. If you specify term_type, you cannot specify due_date, and vice versa. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: items
optional_parameters.description: Array of json objects. Line item information. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: minimumAmountDue
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Base object for all financial value related fields (balance, payment due, etc.). See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: sandbox
optional_parameters.description: Use sandbox to tests. Set 1 to enable.

optional_parameters.name: ccInfo
optional_parameters.description: Array of json objects. Participant information. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: logoUrl
optional_parameters.description: The full URL to an external logo image. Maximum length: 4000.

optional_parameters.name: custom
optional_parameters.description: Json object. The custom amount to apply to an invoice. If you include a label, you must include a custom amount. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: taxInclusive
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the unit price includes tax. Default is false.

optional_parameters.name: templateId
optional_parameters.description: The ID of the template from which to create the invoice. Useful for copy functionality.

optional_parameters.name: discount
optional_parameters.description: Json object. The cost as a percent or an amount value. For example, to specify 10%, enter 10. Alternatively, to specify an amount of 5, enter 5. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: note
optional_parameters.description: A note to the payer. Maximum length: 4000.

optional_parameters.name: reference
optional_parameters.description: Reference data, such as PO number, to add to the invoice. Maximum length: 60.

optional_parameters.name: invoiceDate
optional_parameters.description: The date when the invoice was enabled. The date format is yyyy-MM-dd z.

optional_parameters.name: shippingCost
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Shipping cost, as a percent or an amount value. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: shippingInfo
optional_parameters.description: Json object. Shipping information for the invoice recipient. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: taxCalculatedAfterDiscount
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the tax is calculated before or after a discount. If false, the tax is calculated before a discount. If true, the tax is calculated after a discount. Default is false.

optional_parameters.name: billingInfo
optional_parameters.description: Array of json objects. Billing information for the invoice recipient. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createInvoice README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: merchantMemo
optional_parameters.description: A private bookkeeping memo for the merchant. Maximum length: 150.

optional_parameters.name: number
optional_parameters.description: The unique invoice number. If you omit this number, it is auto-incremented from the previous invoice number. Maximum length: 25.

optional_parameters.name: terms
optional_parameters.description: The general terms of the invoice. Maximum length: 4000.

optional_parameters.name: attachments
optional_parameters.description: The array of files attached to an invoice or template.

optional_parameters.name: allowPartialPayment
optional_parameters.description: Indicates whether the invoice allows a partial payment. If false, invoice must be paid in full. If true, the invoice allows partial payments. Default is false.

api_list.name: createPayment
api_list.description: Use the payment resource for direct credit card payments, stored credit card payments, or PayPal account payments.

required_parameters.name: accessToken
required_parameters.description: accessToken obtained with clientId and secret.

required_parameters.description: Json object. Source of the funds for this payment represented by a PayPal account or a direct credit card. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createPayment README for more details.

required_parameters.description: Json object. Set of redirect URLs you provide only for PayPal-based payments. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createPayment README for more details.

required_parameters.name: intent
required_parameters.description: Payment intent. Must be set to sale for immediate payment, authorize to authorize a payment for capture later, or order to create an order. Allowed values: sale, authorize, order.

required_parameters.name: transactions
required_parameters.description: Array of json objects. Transaction details, if updating a payment. Note that this instance of the transactions object accepts only the amount object. See the parameter notes section for more information. See createPayment README for more details.

optional_parameters.name: experienceProfileId
optional_parameters.description: PayPal generated identifier for the merchant's payment experience profile.

optional_parameters.name: noteToPayer
optional_parameters.description: free-form field for the use of clients to pass in a message to the payer.

optional_parameters.name: sandbox
optional_parameters.description: Use sandbox to tests. Set 1 to enable.

required_parameters.name: authAlgo
required_parameters.description: The algorithm that PayPal uses to generate the signature and that you can use to verify the signature. Extract this value from the PAYPAL-AUTH-ALGO response header, which is received with the webhook notification.

required_parameters.name: transmissionTime
required_parameters.description: The date and time of the HTTP transmission. Contained in the PAYPAL-TRANSMISSION-TIME header of the notification message.

required_parameters.description: accessToken obtained with clientId and secret.

required_parameters.name: certUrl
required_parameters.description: The X.509 public key certificate. Download the certificate from this URL and use it to verify the signature. Extract this value from the PAYPAL-CERT-URL response header, which is received with the webhook notification.

required_parameters.name: webhookId
required_parameters.description: The ID of the webhook as configured in your Developer Portal account.

required_parameters.name: transmissionSig
required_parameters.description: The PayPal-generated asymmetric signature. Extract this value from the PAYPAL-TRANSMISSION-SIG response header, which is received with the webhook notification.
